\begin_layout Paragraph
Issues with the artificial neural network:
\series medium
 
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
There are many problems which have been found during the process of implementing
 the proposed model of Dr.
 Golmohammadi.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
First, the network will not work if we introduce new criteria to our problem
 in our case study (refer to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Case-Study"

\end_inset

).
 This issue happens because the network has only been trained with the training
 data that only contains information related to the provided criteria.
 If we introduce new criteria, the network will stop working because it
 does not have the relevant information about the new criteria.
 In the situation of new criteria being introduced, we have to restart everythin
g from scratch again, in other words, we have to build an entirely new training
 data which contains information about the new criteria so the artificial
 neural network can learn.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Second, if the training data is not well-defined, the performance of the
 artificial neural network will be deeply affected and can not be useful
 anymore.
 Therefore, we have to be extra careful when modeling the training data
 in order not to waste too much time in training the neural network, in
 particular with the case where we have a large set of training data, and
 the architecture of the artificial neural network is complex.
\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Third, this study only scrapes the tip of the iceberg.
 Until now, the artificial neural network seems very simple to us because
 we only pick the most basic and easiest to understand concepts of artificial
 neural network and machine learning in general.
 Looking at the code where we created an instance of artificial neural network
 in MATLAB (refer to 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand formatted
reference "subsec:Artificial-Neural-Network"

\end_inset

), we can see that there are many parameters to be configured.
 Moreover, yet those settings are for the feedforward neural network, the
 simplest kind of artificial neural network.
 Therefore, it is very hard and requires a lot of skill, experience, and
 patient to configure an optimal artificial neural network.
\end_layout

